<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2421">
Calculate the number of ways you can reorder the characters of a string so that no two adjacent characters are the same.<br />
<br />
For example, the answer for <code>aabc</code> is $6$, because the possible orders are <code>abac</code>, <code>abca</code>, <code>acab</code>, <code>acba</code>, <code>baca</code>, and <code>caba</code>.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has a string that consists of $n$ characters between <code>a</code>â€“<code>z</code>.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print an integer: the answer modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 5000$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>aabc</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>6</code>    </div>
